ce:section.ce:para:
Under optimal experimental conditions, we studied the performance of this immunosensor to detect different concentrations of CA 125 and its DPV and SWV responses were recorded in the redox probe solution containing 0.01 M [Fe (CN)6]3−/4− containing KCl. As seen in Figs. 6 and 7

                        , well-defined DPV and SWV responses were observed in the presence of different concentrations of CA 125 and the peak current signals related to [Fe (CN)6]3−/4− decrease with increase of the CA 125 concentration. This suggests that by adding different concentrations of CA 125 to be used as the target on the modified electrode surface, the antibody-antigen interaction was successfully performed. Due to immunocomplex between Ab-Ag the response of the redox probe (0.01 M [Fe (CN)6]3−/4− containing KCl) is reduced and thereby leads to enhanced electron-transfer resistance. The following regression equation between the electrochemical current response and the CA 125 concentration range from 0.01 to 400 U/mL was found. The low limit of quantification for this immunosensor was 0.01 U/mL (Table 1
                        ).
